ally, as you do damage you move up a hate list, we know this, and taunt is suppose to put you 1 point above the highest on the list, if successful.  If a wizard nukes and pulls agro and has a damage sheild, wont that continue to build on his hate ranking?  So, if you taunt to go 1 point above the wizard's hate ranking and the mob punches the wizard after you taunt, wouldn't the damage sheild put the wizard's ranking over yours?  I've always been somewhat unclear on this so I usually don't say anything during group or raid adventures.  But, it's always on my mind and kind of bugs me when a druid will cast his group damage sheild or when a caster of some sort requests a damage sheild.<br><br>Balker Neehigh<br>60 Warlord<br>The Commune<br>Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 3:10:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Damage Sheilds</span><hr size=1> Some ideas/observations regarding aggro:<br><br>-mobs tend to &quot;hate&quot; getting hit frequently more than they hate getting hit hard, even if the resultant damage output is the same.  Might be an artifact of the update/check rate of the hate list; i.e. lots of smaller hits more likely to keep you at the top of the hate list reliably than less frequent big ones would, even if both end up doing the same DPS.<br><br>-mob distance appears to be checked from player's center to mob's center, at least for some calculations.  This may be useful to enhance/reduce the aggro in distance-sensitive fights.<br><br>-should put in some info regarding rampage (or did I miss it?); basically, you want self-healing tanks (paladins ideally) to be on the rampage list before your casters, and rampage appears to be very aggro-order dependent.  Buncha other threads on this tho.<br><br>-even /con'ing a mob can cause it to frenzy and attack; it appears to cause an aggro check vs. the /con-er, and will cause some mobs to attack at ranges greater than they normally would.<br><br>Will think about it a bit more, nice summary so far tho.<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ublaacker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blaacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 9:04:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Damage Sheilds</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, never seen a mob agro due to a con, have I missed something? Remf, as MT in lots of situations, should I &quot;chain-con&quot; the mob?  Never heard that, gonna try it out.  I go with the taunt,disarm,slam, occassional Beg macro routine, but I could certainly throw a con in there. <p>Blaacker<br><br>If I was an Autobot, I'd be:<br><a href="http://android5.com/misc/tests"><img border=0  src="http://android5.com/misc/tests/autobot/ironhide.gif"alt="Click to see what Autobot you could be!"></a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86024" target="new"> See My Gear </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 2:53:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   /con aggro</span><hr size=1> Heyas-<br><br>I really don't think /con builds much/any aggro, but it DOES seem to cause an aggro check and/or initialize a mob's aggro list.  If the mob has a very different &quot;I already know/hate you and I'm gonna attack&quot; range vs. his &quot;ah, I see you now and I'm gonna kill you&quot; range, you can use it to split/pull them.  /Con DOES affect the mob you target.<br><br>To test: find some KOS blue mobs, DONT con them, and stand JUST far enough away that they don't aggro you.  Wait there a bit longer, to really convince yourself they aren't gonna attack.  Now, target the closest one and start spamming /con; it'll aggro and attack.  At level 60, a perfect place to check is FG on the shrooms, or Sol B imps.<br><br>Anyway, I use it to split blue mobs for single pulls, but the effect could also cause unintended aggro on folks, or early placement on the rampage list...<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=541.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=541.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?